translated:
Ögren, Carl Olof, temporary first physician, Jönköping, born 23/6/01 in Blidsberg, Älvsborg County. Son of Carl Ö. and Ida Stenlund. Married in 1936 to Karin Gustafson. Children: Eva Karin, born in 1938, Anna Brita, born in 1942, Sven Olof, born in 1945. 

Education: Passed student exam in Borås in 1920, graduated from Gothenburg Commercial Institute, medical candidate in 1927 and medical licentiate in 1933 in Stockholm. Assistant doctor at Sahlgrunden Hospital Medical Department in 1933, junior doctor at Ulricehamn Sanatorium from 1933-1934, doctor at Djursätra Spa in 1936, at Skagersbrunn in 1936 and 1937, acting assistant and temporary assistant at the Psychiatric Hospital from 1935-1937, assistant there from 1937-1938, temporary second physician there from 1938. Junior doctor at Seraf Hospital Neurology Clinic, second physician at Ryhov Hospital in Jönköping since 1939, acting chief physician at the Mental Illness Department at Jönköping Prison from 1946-1947, temporary first physician there. Psychiatric consultant for the Board of State Occupational Schools in Långanäs since 1943, at Jönköping Public School since 1943, and at Jönköping Child Welfare Board since 1944.
